1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:53.130
Bell-mère

31
00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:54.260
Alright.

32
00:01:54.260 --> 00:01:57.390
Let's hear this reason, then.

33
00:01:57.390 --> 00:01:58.140
I'll pass.

34
00:01:58.140 --> 00:01:59.060
H-Hey!

35
00:01:59.060 --> 00:02:01.480
I don't care about her past.

36
00:02:01.480 --> 00:02:02.850
Where are you going, Luffy?

37
00:02:02.850 --> 00:02:03.900
For a walk.

38
00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:07.320
A-A walk?! You're not
gonna listen to this?!

39
00:02:07.320 --> 00:02:08.520
Nah. Pass.

40
00:02:10.030 --> 00:02:10.990
What's with him?

41
00:02:11.860 --> 00:02:14.610
Don't mind him.
That's just how he is.

42
00:02:14.610 --> 00:02:16.570
We'll hear you out.

43
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:19.950
Though I doubt it'll make
much of a difference.

44
00:02:19.950 --> 00:02:22.540
Yeah! I'll listen, too!

45
00:02:22.540 --> 00:02:25.920
I wanna know what's
happening on this island!

46
00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:28.880
Me, too! I want to know
everything about Nami!

47
00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:32.130
He's out like a light.

48
00:02:32.130 --> 00:02:34.010
Don't sleep right after saying that!

49
00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:38.970
I see.

50
00:02:39.560 --> 00:02:42.060
So this is why Nami
is having such a hard time.

51
00:02:47.860 --> 00:02:48.980
I fell asleep...?

52
00:02:49.650 --> 00:02:50.780
Huh?

53
00:02:50.780 --> 00:02:51.940
Nojiko?

54
00:02:53.570 --> 00:02:55.700
Where could she have gone?

55
00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:04.370
Just a little more, Bell-mère.

56
00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:09.130
Just a little more,
and we'll have it all back.

57
00:03:09.540 --> 00:03:12.340
Cocoyashi Village,
the tangerine orchard,

58
00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:13.970
and even my dream!

59
00:03:20.890 --> 00:03:24.230
It took eight years...

60
00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:37.320
Nami (8 Years Ago)

61
00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:35.240
It's done...

62
00:03:35.650 --> 00:03:37.320
It's done!

63
00:03:45.580 --> 00:03:47.870
Now I just need to check that book...

64
00:03:57.470 --> 00:03:58.590
Oh!

65
00:03:58.590 --> 00:03:59.430
Nami!

66
00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:01.260
What's wrong?

67
00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:04.220
Nothing!

68
00:04:04.220 --> 00:04:06.060
Nothing at all!

69
00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:17.240
Oh, my!

70
00:04:17.530 --> 00:04:19.740
Damn it, Nami!

71
00:04:19.740 --> 00:04:21.700
Not again!

72
00:04:22.030 --> 00:04:23.950
Oh? You did it again, Nami?

73
00:04:22.450 --> 00:04:23.950
Let go!

74
00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:25.240
You just never learn!

75
00:04:25.240 --> 00:04:27.460
I'm not a cat!

76
00:04:27.460 --> 00:04:29.040
You idiot!

77
00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:32.460
Genzo (8 Years Ago)

78
00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:32.130
How many times do I have
to tell you not to steal?!

79
00:04:32.710 --> 00:04:35.960
It's not our fault we're poor!

80
00:04:36.630 --> 00:04:38.420
Cheapskate!

81
00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:40.970
Bell-mère!

82
00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:42.600
Bell-mère!

83
00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:45.140
Your no-good cat's been at it again!

84
00:04:47.390 --> 00:04:50.900
Bell-mère
Nami and Nojiko's
Foster Mother

85
00:04:48.810 --> 00:04:50.900
What is it? Pipe down!

86
00:04:51.520 --> 00:04:52.270
Oh!

87
00:04:52.270 --> 00:04:53.820
Welcome home, Nami!

88
00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:55.020
I'm back!

89
00:04:55.400 --> 00:04:57.900
Look! This is the umpteenth time!

90
00:04:57.900 --> 00:04:59.700
She's infamous in the village now!

91
00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:02.280
Oh? Is that so?

92
00:05:02.780 --> 00:05:06.120
Surely even you've stolen
something before, Mr. Gen?

93
00:05:06.120 --> 00:05:08.250
You're the reason she acts like this!

94
00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:09.870
I'm just kidding!

95
00:05:09.870 --> 00:05:11.250
Look, I get it.

96
00:05:11.250 --> 00:05:13.250
You covered the cost, right?

97
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:15.090
B-Bell-mère...

98
00:05:15.420 --> 00:05:16.710
I can't thank you enough.

99
00:05:16.710 --> 00:05:18.340
Money's a bit tight right now.

100
00:05:18.340 --> 00:05:20.050
I'll pay you back later...

101
00:05:20.590 --> 00:05:22.800
with my body.

102
00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:27.890
I d-didn't mean it l-like that!

103
00:05:28.850 --> 00:05:30.890
You're beet red!

104
00:05:36.070 --> 00:05:38.900
Oh? And why are you laughing?

105
00:05:41.070 --> 00:05:42.450
I'm sorry!

106
00:05:42.950 --> 00:05:46.200
But I really wanted this book!

107
00:05:46.200 --> 00:05:49.580
If you wanted it,
why didn't you just tell me?

108
00:05:50.830 --> 00:05:53.080
You wouldn't have
bought it for me anyway...

109
00:05:53.080 --> 00:05:54.580
Of course I would have!

110
00:05:54.580 --> 00:05:56.710
We've got some money stashed away.

111
00:05:56.710 --> 00:06:00.630
But the villagers said that
the weather's been so good lately,

112
00:06:00.630 --> 00:06:03.550
any old field will grow
tons of tangerines.

113
00:06:03.550 --> 00:06:06.720
We can't get a good price for ours,
and they won't sell anyway.

114
00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:08.850
They can mind their own business!

115
00:06:08.850 --> 00:06:11.270
You're so dumb, Nami!

116
00:06:08.890 --> 00:06:11.270
Nojiko (8 Years Ago)

117
00:06:11.270 --> 00:06:14.060
I would've stolen it way better!

118
00:06:15.310 --> 00:06:17.520
I said no stealing!

119
00:06:18.020 --> 00:06:20.360
I was just joking!

120
00:06:20.360 --> 00:06:21.990
That hurts!

121
00:06:26.530 --> 00:06:28.620
But you know, one thing's for sure!

122
00:06:29.410 --> 00:06:32.330
You really draw some
amazing maps, Nami!

123
00:06:33.460 --> 00:06:36.920
First you learned to draw
sea charts, and now land maps!

124
00:06:38.090 --> 00:06:40.800
This is a map of this island, isn't it?!

125
00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:45.760
No one would ever think
someone your age drew this!

126
00:06:47.390 --> 00:06:50.720
I've been studying navigation, too!

127
00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:52.850
Even navigation?!

128
00:06:52.850 --> 00:06:54.690
That's Nami's dream, after all!

129
00:06:55.060 --> 00:06:56.270
Yeah!

130
00:06:56.270 --> 00:07:00.610
I'm gonna use my navigation skills
to sail all the world's seas!

131
00:07:00.940 --> 00:07:04.360
And then I'll make a map
of everything I see!

132
00:07:05.660 --> 00:07:10.280
That means this map of the island
is the first step towards your dream!

133
00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:12.370
Yeah!

134
00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:15.540
A map of the world, huh?

135
00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:19.500
Nami! Someday, your
dream will come true!

136
00:07:22.590 --> 00:07:24.010
I just know it!

137
00:07:29.180 --> 00:07:30.970
Hey, Bell-mère.

138
00:07:31.810 --> 00:07:33.930
You haven't been eating lately.

139
00:07:34.310 --> 00:07:36.560
I'm eating tangerines, aren't I?

140
00:07:36.560 --> 00:07:37.900
I'm on a diet right now!

141
00:07:38.400 --> 00:07:40.190
I don't need any food, either.

142
00:07:40.190 --> 00:07:42.440
Since when are you
watching your figure?

143
00:07:42.440 --> 00:07:44.570
Kids need to eat right!

144
00:07:44.570 --> 00:07:46.070
Stop lying!

145
00:07:46.070 --> 00:07:50.280
You aren't eating because we
don't have any money, right?

146
00:07:50.280 --> 00:07:50.990
Really?!

147
00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:54.000
You're suffering so that we can–

148
00:07:52.790 --> 00:07:54.000
I'm on a diet!

149
00:07:54.370 --> 00:07:58.250
You shouldn't underestimate
the rejuvenating power of tangerines!

150
00:07:58.250 --> 00:08:03.960
They're the reason I still have such
glowing skin at the age of thirty!

151
00:08:03.960 --> 00:08:05.670
But your hands are yellow.

152
00:08:05.670 --> 00:08:07.630
Just shut up and eat!

153
00:08:09.140 --> 00:08:11.140
Here you go, Nami! It's done!

154
00:08:11.140 --> 00:08:13.850
It's Bell-mère's own
haute couture brand!

155
00:08:13.850 --> 00:08:15.890
Another hand-me-down from Nojiko?

156
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:17.020
Now, now!

157
00:08:17.020 --> 00:08:19.520
It looks great on you, Nami!

158
00:08:19.520 --> 00:08:21.610
This lion used to be a sunflower!

159
00:08:21.610 --> 00:08:23.610
That's just how it goes!

160
00:08:23.610 --> 00:08:26.240
You're two years younger than I am!

161
00:08:26.570 --> 00:08:28.610
Age has nothing to do with it!

162
00:08:28.610 --> 00:08:30.740
I want new clothes, too!

163
00:08:30.740 --> 00:08:32.740
Mine are old clothes, too, you know!

164
00:08:32.740 --> 00:08:36.370
You get my stuff 'cause
you're my baby sister!

165
00:08:36.790 --> 00:08:39.330
But I'm not even your real sister!

166
00:08:39.330 --> 00:08:41.960
We're not related by blood!

167
00:08:42.380 --> 00:08:43.090
Nami!

168
00:08:51.510 --> 00:08:52.850
Bell-mère!

169
00:08:58.850 --> 00:09:01.310
So what if you're not
blood-related?!

170
00:09:04.270 --> 00:09:08.240
Don't say something
that stupid ever again!

171
00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:10.530
Wh-Whatever...

172
00:09:10.530 --> 00:09:15.030
It's not like you're our
real mom, anyway!

173
00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:18.450
You'd be better off
without us, wouldn't you?!

174
00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:21.620
That way, you'd have enough to eat!

175
00:09:21.620 --> 00:09:25.130
You could buy all the clothes
you want! You could be free!

176
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:26.420
I wish...

177
00:09:27.170 --> 00:09:31.090
I wish someone richer
had adopted me instead!

178
00:09:39.020 --> 00:09:39.930
Is...

179
00:09:39.930 --> 00:09:40.940
that so?

180
00:09:42.060 --> 00:09:44.110
Fine, then! Do what you want!

181
00:09:44.110 --> 00:09:47.900
If you hate this house so much,
feel free to go live somewhere else!

182
00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:49.860
Stop it, you two!

183
00:09:50.740 --> 00:09:52.740
Fine! I'm leaving!

184
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:54.530
Nami!

185
00:09:54.950 --> 00:09:56.780
Nami!

186
00:10:04.580 --> 00:10:06.250
Bell-mère...

187
00:10:06.250 --> 00:10:09.510
The three of us are a family!

188
00:10:09.510 --> 00:10:11.590
I bet Nami feels the same way!

189
00:10:11.590 --> 00:10:14.260
She didn't mean what she said!

190
00:10:15.850 --> 00:10:17.560
You're a good girl, Nojiko.

191
00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:20.850
That was real immature of me.

192
00:10:21.430 --> 00:10:23.480
Could you go bring
Nami back for me?

193
00:10:23.480 --> 00:10:26.650
I'll have a super awesome dinner
ready before you get back!

194
00:10:27.570 --> 00:10:28.610
Okay!

195
00:10:36.620 --> 00:10:41.540
Cocoyashi Village

196
00:10:42.330 --> 00:10:44.460
Alright, ma'am! How about this much?

197
00:10:44.460 --> 00:10:47.500
What? Can't you do better than that?

198
00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:50.420
Right over here!
Come see our low prices!

199
00:10:50.420 --> 00:10:55.590
You can't beat my fruit
when it comes to freshness!

200
00:11:03.890 --> 00:11:07.020
So, coming here from the edge
of the village is "running away"?

201
00:11:07.020 --> 00:11:08.520
Must be pretty convenient!

202
00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:12.280
Here. Drink up before it gets cold!

203
00:11:15.150 --> 00:11:18.870
Bell-mère would be
happier if we were gone.

204
00:11:19.620 --> 00:11:20.830
Why do you think that?

205
00:11:21.950 --> 00:11:24.830
Having two kids costs a lot of money,

206
00:11:24.830 --> 00:11:29.210
and everyone in the village
hates her because of me.

207
00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:32.420
You're old enough to
think about others now, huh?

208
00:11:33.670 --> 00:11:35.050
Don't worry.

209
00:11:35.050 --> 00:11:38.890
She was a pretty infamous brat
when she was your age, too.

210
00:11:39.260 --> 00:11:40.600
Really? Bell-mère?

211
00:11:40.600 --> 00:11:44.890
She's still quite an infamous
brat in the villagers' eyes!

212
00:11:45.520 --> 00:11:48.770
Imagine how surprised we were
when she suddenly declared,

213
00:11:48.770 --> 00:11:50.650
"I'm going to be a Marine!"

214
00:11:50.650 --> 00:11:51.980
A Marine?!

215
00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:54.070
Bell-mère was a Marine?!

216
00:11:54.440 --> 00:11:55.530
Yeah...

217
00:12:03.950 --> 00:12:08.460
"Pirates have to pay for
slaughtering innocent people!"

218
00:12:08.460 --> 00:12:10.920
With those words, she left the village.

219
00:12:18.630 --> 00:12:22.350
Just as she thought her
time had finally come...

220
00:12:23.850 --> 00:12:26.640
Well... I guess this is it...

221
00:12:45.490 --> 00:12:47.000
Is that your baby sister?

222
00:12:51.920 --> 00:12:54.380
Nuh-uh. I dunno who she is.

223
00:13:04.140 --> 00:13:06.310
She has no idea what's going on...

224
00:13:21.320 --> 00:13:22.780
Nami, that girl...

225
00:13:22.780 --> 00:13:24.070
was you.

226
00:13:25.120 --> 00:13:30.040
When she saw you, Bell-mère
mustered up the will to live again.

227
00:13:40.380 --> 00:13:42.590
It is a boat! I knew it!

228
00:13:42.590 --> 00:13:45.850
On a stormy night like tonight?!
Who the hell could it be?!

229
00:13:54.770 --> 00:13:55.980
Doctor!

230
00:13:55.980 --> 00:13:57.400
Get the doctor!

231
00:13:58.030 --> 00:14:00.650
Bell-mère? Is that you, Bell-mère?!

232
00:14:00.650 --> 00:14:01.490
Bell-mère!

233
00:14:01.490 --> 00:14:03.240
What in the world happened?!

234
00:14:06.740 --> 00:14:07.530
Who are these–

235
00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:09.790
Doctor! They have terrible fevers!

236
00:14:09.790 --> 00:14:12.080
They're exhausted from the storm!

237
00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:13.330
What?!

238
00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:16.540
R-Right, got it!

239
00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:19.460
But we need to tend to those
nasty wounds of yours, too!

240
00:14:19.460 --> 00:14:21.420
Forget about that! Just hurry!

241
00:14:21.420 --> 00:14:23.720
Please! Don't let them die!

242
00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:25.510
Save them!

243
00:14:26.220 --> 00:14:30.430
I beg of you!

244
00:14:32.680 --> 00:14:35.900
A delinquent like you...
What did you just say?!

245
00:14:36.520 --> 00:14:40.150
I said that I'm going
to be their mother.

246
00:14:40.150 --> 00:14:41.400
You can't!

247
00:14:41.400 --> 00:14:42.900
Don't do it!

248
00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:45.610
A punk like you can't
possibly raise children!

249
00:14:45.610 --> 00:14:49.660
L-Listen to me! Give them
to a government institution!

250
00:14:49.660 --> 00:14:51.290
I've already made up my mind!

251
00:14:52.410 --> 00:14:54.420
I'm an adult now, too.

252
00:14:54.420 --> 00:14:56.040
I was even a Marine.

253
00:14:56.040 --> 00:14:58.670
I've tried to become more
of a decent human being.

254
00:14:58.670 --> 00:15:01.510
I'm going to be responsible
for raising these kids.

255
00:15:02.630 --> 00:15:04.470
I'll raise them to be good people.

256
00:15:04.470 --> 00:15:06.930
The kind who won't be
corrupted by the world.

257
00:15:07.760 --> 00:15:10.470
I'm going to live on with these girls.

258
00:15:10.470 --> 00:15:13.770
Nami and Nojiko saved my life.

259
00:15:18.730 --> 00:15:23.570
The bond you three have
runs far deeper than blood.

260
00:15:27.660 --> 00:15:29.910
Nami! I thought you'd be here!

261
00:15:29.910 --> 00:15:31.660
N-Nojiko!

262
00:15:32.040 --> 00:15:34.250
Bell-mère is waiting for us!

263
00:15:34.790 --> 00:15:36.620
She's making a yummy dinner!

264
00:15:38.630 --> 00:15:39.590
Okay!

265
00:15:40.290 --> 00:15:42.090
I bet it's your favorite!

266
00:15:42.090 --> 00:15:43.840
Omelets with tangerine sauce!

267
00:15:43.840 --> 00:15:45.510
Yahoo!

268
00:15:47.050 --> 00:15:51.180
– Yay! Omelets!
– Yay! Omelets!

269
00:15:55.480 --> 00:15:57.980
Pirates, everyone!

270
00:15:58.600 --> 00:16:00.650
Pirates are coming!

271
00:16:01.690 --> 00:16:02.940
Pirates!

272
00:16:02.940 --> 00:16:05.820
Everyone hide!

273
00:16:14.700 --> 00:16:16.250
It's the Arlong Pirates!

274
00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:17.040
Arlong?!

275
00:16:17.040 --> 00:16:17.960
That can't be!

276
00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:21.380
Wh-What are fishmen from
the Grand Line doing here?!

277
00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:24.920
Was the rumor about a split
in the Fishman Pirates true?

278
00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:26.550
Nami! Nojiko!

279
00:16:26.550 --> 00:16:27.670
Mr. Gen!

280
00:16:28.180 --> 00:16:29.800
It's dangerous here!

281
00:16:29.800 --> 00:16:31.470
Go and hide in the woods!

282
00:16:31.800 --> 00:16:32.970
Huh? But...

283
00:16:32.970 --> 00:16:34.560
Go! Now!

284
00:16:45.730 --> 00:16:49.150
You seem to be in high spirits
for a bunch of pathetic humans!

285
00:16:49.150 --> 00:16:54.410
As of this moment, this village– No, this entire island is under my control!

286
00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:58.290
Listen up!

287
00:16:58.290 --> 00:17:02.920
On this glorious day, you will
all buy your lives from me!

288
00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:07.380
You'll pay 100,000 per adult.

289
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:09.300
Each child is 50,000.

290
00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:11.720
Those who can't pay will die!

291
00:17:14.010 --> 00:17:16.470
What do we do, Nojiko?

292
00:17:16.850 --> 00:17:19.100
We can't pay that much!

293
00:17:19.100 --> 00:17:21.600
But they might not spot our house!

294
00:17:21.600 --> 00:17:23.480
You can't see it from the village!

295
00:17:28.360 --> 00:17:30.570
How much did we get, brother?

296
00:17:31.070 --> 00:17:33.530
Just over 25 million, I'd say.

297
00:17:34.160 --> 00:17:35.240
Excellent!

298
00:17:39.830 --> 00:17:45.090
Sounds like we have to pay 100,000 berries
every month for the rest of our lives!

299
00:17:45.090 --> 00:17:47.460
Pay 100,000...?! We can't
 even survive like that!

300
00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:48.710
Endure it for now!

301
00:17:48.710 --> 00:17:52.180
We should just be grateful
no one in the village was killed.

302
00:17:52.760 --> 00:17:56.390
If it's only money they want,
that's an easy price to pay.

303
00:17:56.720 --> 00:18:02.350
I just hope they leave without
seeing Bell-mère's house.

304
00:18:02.980 --> 00:18:06.230
With the two children, it would
come to 200,000 berries...

305
00:18:06.230 --> 00:18:08.820
I doubt she has that much saved up.

306
00:18:09.320 --> 00:18:13.490
Alright! Time to go, brothers!

307
00:18:16.620 --> 00:18:19.580
Captain Arlong! There's smoke
coming from over there!

308
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:27.290
Okay!

309
00:18:27.290 --> 00:18:28.750
Alright, let's see!

310
00:18:29.170 --> 00:18:33.010
That's too good! Nothing's quite like
Bell-mère's special tangerine sauce!

311
00:18:33.010 --> 00:18:35.970
Nami and Nojiko are gonna
leap out of their seats!

312
00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:38.890
The smoke is coming from a house!

313
00:18:39.850 --> 00:18:41.220
Oh?

314
00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:42.810
We almost missed it.

315
00:18:42.810 --> 00:18:44.270
Damn!

316
00:18:44.270 --> 00:18:46.150
– Bell-mère!
– Bell-mère!

317
00:18:47.020 --> 00:18:49.110
Come on! Let's go collect our money!

318
00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:53.360
Oh no, this is bad! The pirates...

319
00:18:53.360 --> 00:18:55.160
...are headed to Bell-mère's house!

320
00:18:59.450 --> 00:19:01.540
Hey! Nojiko and Nami are gone!

321
00:19:01.870 --> 00:19:02.620
What?!

322
00:19:03.290 --> 00:19:05.670
Ten more minutes
for the duck in the oven.

323
00:19:05.670 --> 00:19:07.290
The stew is boiling.

324
00:19:07.290 --> 00:19:09.340
This'll really mess up our budget,

325
00:19:09.340 --> 00:19:12.550
but sometimes you've gotta splurge!

326
00:19:19.350 --> 00:19:22.430
Bell-mère's gonna...
Bell-mère's gonna...

327
00:19:24.430 --> 00:19:26.440
Bell-mère's gonna be killed!

328
00:19:33.990 --> 00:19:37.070
We can't just abandon Bell-mère!

329
00:19:37.070 --> 00:19:39.620
Damn! Why did this have to happen?!

330
00:19:39.620 --> 00:19:41.370
Don't jump the gun, Bell-mère!

331
00:19:44.790 --> 00:19:46.330
Oh, are they back?

332
00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:55.420
It's open!

333
00:19:55.420 --> 00:19:57.220
Come on in!

334
00:19:57.590 --> 00:19:58.800
Pardon me...

335
00:20:22.990 --> 00:20:24.330
You've got bad luck.

336
00:20:24.330 --> 00:20:26.080
I'm a former Marine.

337
00:20:26.830 --> 00:20:32.540
What are pirates from the Grand Line doing out here in Cocoyashi Village?

338
00:20:37.130 --> 00:20:38.130
What's so funny?!

339
00:20:45.180 --> 00:20:49.690
Weak! Weak! You're weak!
So weak! So, so weak!

340
00:20:49.690 --> 00:20:54.070
Your inferior species is just so weak!

341
00:21:01.320 --> 00:21:03.990
Let's escape with her
out the back door!

342
00:21:03.990 --> 00:21:05.790
But they might already be there!

343
00:21:05.790 --> 00:21:06.750
We'll be fine!

344
00:21:06.750 --> 00:21:07.660
Hold it!

345
00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:12.670
Doctor!

346
00:21:12.670 --> 00:21:13.750
You mustn't go home!

347
00:21:13.750 --> 00:21:14.500
Wha...?!

348
00:21:14.500 --> 00:21:16.710
Move! We have to save Bell-mère!

349
00:21:16.710 --> 00:21:18.090
Nojiko! Nami!

350
00:21:18.590 --> 00:21:20.720
Listen closely, you two!

351
00:21:20.720 --> 00:21:21.890
This isn't the time to–

352
00:21:21.890 --> 00:21:23.720
Actually, this is the perfect time...

353
00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:26.640
I have to tell you something horrible!

354
00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:29.100
Doctor?

355
00:21:31.230 --> 00:21:33.520
Bell-mère!

356
00:21:41.610 --> 00:21:45.780
I can't do anything!
These guys are real monsters!

357
00:21:45.780 --> 00:21:46.740
I'm gonna die!

358
00:21:47.200 --> 00:21:49.200
Nojiko! Nami!

359
00:21:49.200 --> 00:21:50.710
Bell-mère!

360
00:21:51.210 --> 00:21:53.630
Don't throw your life
away over your pride!

361
00:21:54.080 --> 00:21:55.670
Some fights aren't worth it!

362
00:21:55.670 --> 00:21:58.710
Some issues can be
solved with money!

363
00:21:58.710 --> 00:22:00.090
Mr. Gen...

364
00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:03.470
That's right, Miss Marine.

365
00:22:03.470 --> 00:22:06.470
It's 100,000 per adult
and 50,000 per child.

366
00:22:06.810 --> 00:22:10.810
Pay for your whole family if you want
to live. Be grateful I'm even telling you.

367
00:22:10.810 --> 00:22:12.060
My whole family?

368
00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:16.650
That's 200,000 in total.

369
00:22:16.650 --> 00:22:18.690
How much do you have, all together?

370
00:22:19.690 --> 00:22:21.700
Including what I've squirreled away...

371
00:22:21.700 --> 00:22:22.900
a little over 100,000...

372
00:22:24.910 --> 00:22:28.240
Hey! There's a meal for
three people in here!

373
00:22:29.160 --> 00:22:30.000
Oh?

374
00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:32.160
A family of three, huh?

375
00:22:34.170 --> 00:22:36.460
I almost forgot!

376
00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:42.170
She invited my friend and me
to dinner tonight!

377
00:22:42.170 --> 00:22:43.800
Come on, Bell-mère.

378
00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:45.890
Hurry and pay your amount.

379
00:22:45.890 --> 00:22:48.350
Our delicious dinner will get cold!

380
00:22:48.350 --> 00:22:49.310
Mr. Gen...

381
00:22:49.310 --> 00:22:51.600
I hear you've got 100,000.

382
00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:53.140
Thank goodness you have enough!

383
00:22:53.980 --> 00:22:56.310
Now everyone in the village can live!

384
00:22:56.690 --> 00:22:57.940
It's true.

385
00:22:57.940 --> 00:23:02.190
The village register has no record
of her getting married or giving birth.

386
00:23:02.190 --> 00:23:04.070
She's single.

387
00:23:08.120 --> 00:23:09.870
Do you understand?!

388
00:23:09.870 --> 00:23:13.370
There's no proof that you two
and Bell-mère are family!

389
00:23:13.370 --> 00:23:16.120
Leave this island before
they take notice of you!

390
00:23:16.120 --> 00:23:17.380
Escape across the sea!

391
00:23:18.380 --> 00:23:20.880
Then all three of you can survive!

392
00:23:21.630 --> 00:23:25.130
It's reckless to send you two
out to sea at such a young age.

393
00:23:25.130 --> 00:23:28.470
A lot could go wrong,
but at least you'll have–

394
00:23:28.470 --> 00:23:29.100
No.

395
00:23:30.600 --> 00:23:32.390
I don't want to.

396
00:23:32.390 --> 00:23:36.270
I... want to live in this village...

397
00:23:36.270 --> 00:23:37.690
Is it because we're poor?

398
00:23:38.150 --> 00:23:41.520
Is that why we can't be
Bell-mère's kids anymore?!

399
00:23:41.900 --> 00:23:44.990
Why? Why?!

400
00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:49.490
Thank goodness.

401
00:23:49.490 --> 00:23:51.240
Then everything will be fine.

402
00:23:51.740 --> 00:23:53.830
Alright, we'll leave the village!

403
00:23:52.660 --> 00:23:53.830
Nojiko!

404
00:23:53.830 --> 00:23:54.960
Let's go!

405
00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:57.420
This way Bell-mère gets to live!

406
00:24:12.930 --> 00:24:14.180
Hold it.

407
00:24:14.180 --> 00:24:16.390
Who said I paid for myself?

408
00:24:17.730 --> 00:24:20.230
That 100,000 is
for my two daughters.

409
00:24:20.860 --> 00:24:22.070
Not for me.

410
00:24:24.320 --> 00:24:25.740
Bell-mère! What are you–

411
00:24:25.740 --> 00:24:27.200
I'm sorry, Mr. Gen.

412
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:30.320
I can't just say I don't have a family.

413
00:24:30.320 --> 00:24:33.030
Even if it costs me my life.

414
00:24:35.200 --> 00:24:36.160
That fool...!

415
00:24:36.500 --> 00:24:39.500
Yeah, maybe we're not
related by blood...

416
00:24:40.670 --> 00:24:42.170
but we're a family.

417
00:24:42.790 --> 00:24:45.130
I want to be their mom,
even if it's only in name.

418
00:24:46.670 --> 00:24:47.970
They're...

419
00:24:48.430 --> 00:24:49.630
my girls.

420
00:24:50.550 --> 00:24:53.260
– Bell-mère!
– Bell-mère!

421
00:24:51.470 --> 00:24:52.640
Wait, you two!

422
00:24:53.680 --> 00:24:57.230
I wish someone richer
had adopted me instead!

423
00:24:57.600 --> 00:24:59.480
It was just a lie!

424
00:24:59.480 --> 00:25:01.100
I was lying!

425
00:25:01.100 --> 00:25:03.820
– Bell-mère!
– Bell-mère!

426
00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:18.620
I wanted...

427
00:25:18.620 --> 00:25:21.790
to buy you lots more
books and clothes...

428
00:25:22.420 --> 00:25:23.630
I'm sorry!

429
00:25:23.630 --> 00:25:26.170
I wish I could've been
a better mother!

430
00:25:26.170 --> 00:25:27.510
That's not true!

431
00:25:27.510 --> 00:25:29.380
We don't need anything!
Just don't die!

432
00:25:29.380 --> 00:25:30.880
Stay with us forever!

433
00:25:30.880 --> 00:25:34.180
I want you to see the map
of the world I'm gonna draw!

434
00:25:36.140 --> 00:25:37.600
Yeah... your map...

435
00:25:38.520 --> 00:25:39.770
Make your dream...

436
00:25:40.270 --> 00:25:42.150
come true!

437
00:25:44.110 --> 00:25:45.570
Live!

438
00:25:45.570 --> 00:25:47.650
Bell-mère!

439
00:25:50.240 --> 00:25:52.570
These are your girls, I take it?

440
00:25:54.780 --> 00:25:56.450
Yeah, that's right!

441
00:25:56.910 --> 00:25:59.500
Promise me you won't
lay a hand on them!

442
00:25:59.500 --> 00:26:00.870
Of course!

443
00:26:00.870 --> 00:26:02.830
As long as you follow
the rules and die!

444
00:26:02.830 --> 00:26:04.630
Help us!

445
00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:18.560
Now they're thirsty for blood...

446
00:26:18.560 --> 00:26:21.020
Don't kill them. Just handle
them as you see fit.

447
00:26:21.390 --> 00:26:24.350
Perfect timing for our
first example to the others!

448
00:26:29.820 --> 00:26:31.400
Die for your worthless love.

449
00:26:41.660 --> 00:26:43.290
Nojiko! Nami!

450
00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:47.460
I love you!
